# VinylMania Support

Welcome to the VinylMania support page. Here you'll find information to help you get the most from your vinyl record experience.

## FAQ

### How do I record vinyl to the app?
1. Connect your turntable to your iOS device using an audio interface
2. Tap the "Record Vinyl" button from the main player screen
3. Configure your recording settings and press record
4. The app will detect track breaks automatically or you can manually set them

### How do I import existing audio files?
1. Navigate to "Vinyl Records" from the main screen
2. Tap the "+" icon in the top right corner
3. You can import audio from Files, other apps, or use the "Import from GarageBand/Logic" option

### Why doesn't my album artwork appear?
Album artwork needs to be either:
- Added during the import process
- Added to an existing album via the album details page

### How do I use the equalizer?
1. During playback, tap the equalizer icon
2. Choose a preset or adjust each frequency band manually
3. Your settings will be saved automatically for future playback

### Can I delete individual tracks?
Yes! In the Vinyl Records view, swipe left on any track to reveal the delete option.

## Troubleshooting

### App crashes during recording
- Ensure your iOS device has sufficient storage
- Try recording at a lower sample rate
- Make sure microphone permissions are enabled in iOS Settings

### Audio playback issues
- Check that your audio file is in a supported format (MP3, WAV, M4A, AAC, AIF, AIFF)
- Try restarting the app
- Ensure your device's volume is turned up

## Feature Requests and Bug Reports

We're constantly improving VinylMania! If you encounter any bugs or have suggestions for new features, please:

1. Check the [existing issues](https://github.com/your-username/VinylMania/issues) to see if it's already reported
2. Create a [new issue](https://github.com/your-username/VinylMania/issues/new) with detailed information about your request or the bug you encountered

